By Onyebuchi Ezigbo in Abuja The National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Adams Oshiomhole, is currently meeting with the chairman of the party’s national convention committee, Jigawa State Governor Abubakar Badaru; Zamfara State Governor Abdulaziz Yari and the Attorney General of the Federation, Abubakar Malami, at his campaign office in Abuja. Although the purpose of the closed-door meeting was not disclosed, THISDAY learnt that it may not be unconnected with issues arising from the last national convention of the party.
Also because governor Yari chaired the panel that conducted the governorship primary for Osun State, it is expected that his preliminary report will form part of their deliberations. Details later…